<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1733,1983]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32">
The genus comprises more then 
<number box="[540,570,1733,1759]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" value="30.0">30</number>
Palaearctic and Australasian species. The Palaearctic fauna was revised recently by 
<bibRefCitation author="Danzig" box="[293,467,1770,1796]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" refString="Danzig, E. M. (1998) Kiritshenkella and related genera of mealybugs from Russia and neighbouring countries (Homoptera: Coccinea: Pseudococcidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 7, 153 - 161." type="journal article" year="1998">
Danzig (
<number box="[396,458,1770,1796]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[526,755,1770,1796]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" refString="Kwon, G. M., Danzig, E. &amp; Park, K. T. (2003) Taxonomic notes of the family Pseudococcidae (Sternorrhyncha) in Korea. II. Tribe Pseudococcini. Insecta Koreana, 20 (3 / 4), 393 - 424." type="journal article">
Kwon 
<emphasis box="[607,659,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[684,747,1770,1796]" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and represented by a compact group of morphologically similar species inhabiting mainly the leaf sheaths of different grasses. The adult females of Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName box="[151,322,1845,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Balanococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="32">Balanococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. are similar in their morphology and mode of life to females of the widely distributed 
<taxonomicName authority="Berg" authorityName="Berg" box="[151,345,1882,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Trionymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,276,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="32">Trionymus</emphasis>
Berg
</taxonomicName>
, but differ in 
<taxonomicName box="[512,680,1883,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Balanococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[512,680,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="32">Balanococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having diagnostically-shaped tubular ducts, with a deep collar covering the duct, and some other small characters, such as short antennae, comparatively large hind coxae and poorly developed ostioles.
</paragraph>
